title: Album Title: Kaleidoscope
body:
Maybe the pink hair was a nod to “I knew you were trouble” where she says “I think when it’s all over it just comes back in flashes, you know? It’s like a kaleidoscope of memories; it just all comes back. But he never does.“

This, plus all of the other kaleidoscope references in the video (they’re dancing in one, there’s one on a coat, plus she says spelling is fun and it’s not an easy word to spell)… I’m convinced!

Then again, the “Home” theories are pretty compelling…

@taylorswift @taylornation

body:
Tour theory

So like I’m a dumbass so I’m just gonna wait for Taylor to tell us the album name, but I’ve been thinking about how she’s gonna do this song live on tour since Brendan Urie’s on it. With End Game she just cut out the other parts, but that would be half of her lead single for this album so I don’t think she’d do that. But for Red tour, she brought Ed with her (not just for their song together but it was definitely a benefit). So I think maybe this means Panic will be touring with her???? They might be too large because they can sell out arenas on their own, but this is my pile of garbage and I’m sticking to it.
